	<p><em><strong>Max</strong> replies:</em> Strictly for the birds?<br />Have you noticed how the words "immigration" and "emigration" are bandied about without their demeaning significance being realised?<br />Birds migrate, workers emigrate and immigrate, but the wealthy capitalist class "take up residence".</p>
	<small>
	written 3rd May 2005 <!-- | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=1705&amp;commentid=2697">abusive?</a>
    --> </small>
	</dd>
	<dd><a name="comment_2779" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>biscuit</strong> replies:</em> i'm migrating.</p> <p>thank you Britain for my excellent education, my degree. now i have a student debt of £12000, so i'm off to distant shores from where i can ridicule you Britain, and never pay back a penny you've so generously spent on me. My loan will be wiped out when i'm finally declared bankrupt next month, so if I do fancy visiting these shores again, the tax man can go F himself.</p> <p>What else do you want me to do? Live in a country governed by Dr Evil himself George Bush. I don't think so. Stay and work for a system that makes life easier for the rich, and harder for the poor. Exist in this dull, retail therapy society with no culture or reason for existance? I'll enjoy myself very much making a life in Brasil thank you very much. My education will be much more worthwhile there.</p> <p>So I'm not voting, one, because I'm out of here forever, and two, because we didn't even get to vote in the election that decided the government to lead our truly 'democratic' country. It happened in 2004, about 5000 miles west of here.</p>
	<small>
	written 3rd May 2005 <!-- | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=1705&amp;commentid=2779">abusive?</a>
    --> </small>
	</dd>
